colorpick - simple X11 color picker
===================================
colorpick is an utility to display the color of a window pixel for X.

Requirements
------------
In order to build dwm you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (colorpick is installed into
/usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install colorpick:

    make clean install



Using colorpick
---------------
When you run colorpick it will wait for a mouse click event. When that
happens, colorpick prints the color of the clicked pixel in hexadecimal
format.


Configuration
-------------
There is no configuration options.
